<html><head><title>Chris Webster</title><meta name="Author" Content="Chris Webster"></head><body><body bgcolor=#ffffff text=#000000 link=#000066 vlink=#bf0000 alink=#ff0000><a href="mailto:cwebster@compulinks.com"><img src=chris.gif border=0 align=left></a><h1>Yep... That's Me!</h1><i>(Immortalized by Jeff Maltby)</i><p><hr><p><font size=+2><b>H</b></font>ello and welcome to my home on the web. My name's Chris. I'm the Owner of <b><a href="../">CompuLink Services</a></b> and the creator of the CompuLink web site (among others). I got into computers about 10 years ago and have loved them ever since. I build computers, enjoy programming, and enjoy desktop publishing as well. I often thought publishing and programming was a strange mix, but the Web has proved me wrong. <br clear=all><hr><table border=0 cellspacing=4 cellpadding=0><tr><td rowspan=7 valign=top width=180><b><font size=+1>A bit about me:</font></td><td align=right><b>Age: </b></td><td> 32</td></tr><tr><td align=right><b>Married: </b></td><td> 9 Years</td></tr><tr><td align=right><b>Children: </b></td><td> Soon... Soon...</td></tr><tr><td align=right><b>Hobbies: </b></td><td> <a href="#music">Music</a> (Playing piano since I was five)</td></tr><tr><td align=right><b>Coffee: </b></td><td> Between 3 - 12 cups a day</td></tr><tr><td align=right><b>Beer: </b></td><td> 1 or 2 in the evening</td></tr></table><a name="music"></a><hr><table border=0 cellspaceing=10 cellpadding=0><tr><td valign=top width=120><h2>Music... <br>Music... <br>Music...</td><td><font size=+2><b>O</b></font>ne of the things I enjoy most about computers is creating music. I'm posting some songs below, but please read the following notes first. <ul><li>You'll need the <b><a href="http://www.realaudio.com">RealAudio Player</a></b> in order to listen. <li>If you have a 28.8 modem, you can listen <i>during</i> the download, otherwise, you'll have to download first. <li>There isn't a single <i>real</i> instrument. The "band" consists of a Yamaha SY22 Synth and a TG500 Tone Generator. <li>I have no fancy recording or mixing equipment of any kind. <li>All parts (horns, percussion, etc.) are played by me on the SY22. <li>If you find the songs disgusting, distasteful, and they make your ears bleed, then please discontinue use. :-) </ul></td></tr></table><font size=+2><b>N</b></font>ow that I've got myself covered, here they are so far: <center><p><img src=line.gif><table border=0 width=585 cellspacing=2><tr><td rowspan=2 valign=top align=center width=60><b><a href="/cgi-bin/redirect/cwebster/music.log/http://www.compulinks.com/me/mass.ram"><img src="speaker.gif" border=0><br>28.8</a></b></td><td valign=top align=center width=435><b><a href="/cgi-bin/redirect/cwebster/music.log/http://www.compulinks.com/me/mass.ram">Mass Transit <i>(3:39 - 406K)</i></a></b></td><td rowspan=2 valign=top align=center width=60><b><a href="/cgi-bin/redirect/cwebster/music.log/http://www.compulinks.com/me/mass.ra"><img src="speaker.gif" border=0><br>14.4</a></b></td></tr><tr><td>This is the first song I wrote after getting my first sound card. Since then it's been repatched to the SY22 and again to the TG500. Some portions are still from the original which was entered on a <i>computer</i> keyboard.</td></tr></table><img src=line.gif><table border=0 width=585 cellspacing=2><tr><td rowspan=2 valign=top align=center width=60><b><a href="/cgi-bin/redirect/cwebster/music.log/http://www.compulinks.com/me/kiwi.ram"><img src="speaker.gif" border=0><br>28.8</a></b></td><td valign=top align=center width=455><b><a href="/cgi-bin/redirect/cwebster/music.log/http://www.compulinks.com/me/kiwi.ram">Kiwi Soup <i>(2:18 - 256K)</i></a></b></td><td rowspan=2 valign=top align=center width=60><b><a href="/cgi-bin/redirect/cwebster/music.log/http://www.compulinks.com/me/kiwi.ra"><img src="speaker.gif" border=0><br>14.4</a></b></td></tr><tr><td>This is the second song I wrote, just after getting the SY22. It sort of "fell" together in about an hour.</td></tr></table><img src=line.gif><p><font size=+2><b>T</b></font>hat's it for now... more coming soon! </center><br><hr><address><font size>Copyright &#169  1996 by <a href="mailto:cwebster@compulinks.com">Chris Webster</a>. All Rights Reserved.</font></address></body></html>
