<html><head><title>The Informed Investor Newsletter - Mutual Fund News</title></head><body background="../images/tile.gif" bgcolor=#ffffff link=#297b63 vlink=#297b63 alink=#31ad84><a href="../index.html"><img src="../images/home.gif" width=55 height=16 align=right border=0 alt="Home" vspace=5 hspace=5></a>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <img src="../titles/mutual.gif"><p><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=6><tr><td><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2></td><td><b>BPI Mutual Funds</b> have recently announced the addition of <b>BPI Asia Pacific Fund</b> to their family of funds. The Asia Pacific Fund will invest in equities doing business in Asia and the Pacific Rim countries, but excluding Japan. <b>Asian Strategic Investment</b> <b>Management</b> is the new managers. Call your financial advisor to get a prospectus and details.<p><b>Canada Trust</b> has just introduced the <b>Global Growth Fund</b>. Canada Trust claim that this fund is the first unrestricted no-load global equity fund for retail investors that allows 100% RSP/RIF eligibility. The Global Growth Fund will be managed by Canada Trust Investment Management with <b>Newcastle Capital Management</b> as advisors.<p><b>Investors Group</b> have announced a 20.1% increase in income for the first nine months of 1996. Mutual fund sales were up 40% for the same period, while asset growth were up 22% for the past twelve months.<b> Mackenzie Financial</b> has just reported thirty percent earnings' gains in the past quarter. Over the past year, mutual fund assets grew by 32%.<p><b>Scotiabank</b> has just announced a new fund, the <b>Scotia Excelsior European Growth Fund. </b>This fund invests in listed equities in EEC countries and will also attempt to capitalize on the privatization trend in Eastern Europe. The European growth fund may be invested in RRSP/RIF's up to the 20% foreign content limit. Call 1800-268-9269 for more information.<p><b>Scotiabank</b> has also launched a new service called the <b>Scotia Leaders Program</b>, a mathematically-designed system that enables Canadians to invest in a variety of consistently above-average performing mutual funds. Two portfolios are offered; global equity and Canadian equity. Each portfolio contains five top performing funds selected from hundreds of funds from well known companies. Minimum investment in the program is five thousand dollars rising to twenty-five thousand on March 1,1997. For more information, call Scotia Leaders Program at 1800-528-3211. On the Internet, go to Scotiabank's site at <b>www.scotiabank.ca</b>. </td><td> &nbsp</td><td background="../images/tbltile.gif" bgcolor=#c6d6c6 valign=top><center><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2><br><img src="../images/charts.gif" width=80 height=15><font face="Arial" size=-1><hr noshade color=#297b63></center>There are no<br>charts related<br>to this article.</font><p></td></tr></table><p><p><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left><hr noshade color=#297b63><table border=0 width=100%><tr><td align=center><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left><a href="canada.html"><img src="../images/back.gif" width=55 height=16 border=0 align=left></a><a href="bonds.html"><img src="../images/next.gif" width=51 height=16 border=0 align=right></a><a href="index.html#contents"><img src="../images/contents.gif" width=106 height=16 border=0></a></td></tr></table><p><p><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left><center><address><font size=-1><a href="../copyright.html">Copyright and Disclaimer</a></center><p><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left><hr noshade><center><address><font size=-1><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left>Site design by <a href="http://www.compulinks.com">CompuLink Services</a>.<br><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left>Contact <a href="mailto:webmaster@compulinks.com">webmaster@compulinks.com</a> with comme