<html><head><title>The Informed Investor Newsletter - US Equity Funds</title></head><body background="../images/tile.gif" bgcolor=#ffffff link=#297b63 vlink=#297b63 alink=#31ad84><a href="../index.html"><img src="../images/home.gif" width=55 height=16 align=right border=0 alt="Home" vspace=5 hspace=5></a>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <img src="../titles/us.gif"><p><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=6><tr><td><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2></td><td><font size=-1 face=Arial><img src="../letters/t.gif" align=left vspace=1 hspace=1>he big news from the US equity markets is that the Dow Jones Industrial Average has finally broken to new highs, projecting a move to the 6200-6400 point zone for a gain of about 7%. The Dow may go higher, but we will have to play along as the market moves higher. Although the Nasdaq index has yet to clear previous highs, it is moving at a faster rate than the other US indices. Still, the Nasdaq, Dow, S&P 500 and the NY Composite are all performing in the upper third of my fifty International indices and sub indices. The one holdout is Biotechnology, which is lagging at the moment.<p>The Investment Funds Institute (US) announced last week that the 6007 (!!) US mutual funds now had $3.12 billion in investment funds, about half in stock funds and about one quarter each in bond/income and money market funds. Mutual fund assets are now second in size to commercial banks but ahead of private pension fund assets. Fund growth over the past six months has been about thirteen percent. The Investment Funds Institute (US) estimates that fund assets have grown by 54% from new cash flow and 46% from price appreciation.<p>On a humorous note, prankster Michael Moore is having a go at greed among presidential candidates. His strategy is to mail small campaign donations from inappropriate-but fictitious-organizations to see which candidates put money before principle.<p>The Perot organization returned a $100 contribution from "Pedophiles for Free Trade". Clinton's campaign cashed a donation from "Hemp Growers of America," while Buchanan's campaign happily cashed a cheque from "Abortionists for Buchanan" in the belief (they said) that the practical jokester would be punished through his own pocketbook. </td><td> &nbsp</td><td background="../images/tbltile.gif" bgcolor=#c6d6c6 valign=top><center><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2><br><img src="../images/charts.gif" width=80 height=15><font face="Arial" size=-1><hr noshade color=#297b63></center>Note: Charts are<br>designed for full<br>screen viewing.<p><center><b><a href="charts/dowjones.gif">Dow Jones<p></a><a href="charts/nasdaq.gif">NASDAQ<p></a><a href="charts/cboebiot.gif">CBOE Biotech<p></a><a href="charts/sp500.gif">SP 500<p></a></td></tr></table><p><p><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left><hr noshade color=#297b63><table border=0 width=100%><tr><td align=center><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left><a href="bonds.html"><img src="../images/back.gif" width=55 height=16 border=0 align=left></a><a href="inter.html"><img src="../images/next.gif" width=51 height=16 border=0 align=right></a><a href="index.html#contents"><img src="../images/contents.gif" width=106 height=16 border=0></a></td></tr></table><p><p><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left><center><address><font size=-1><a href="../copyright.html">Copyright and Disclaimer</a></center><p><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left><hr noshade><center><address><font size=-1><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left>Site design by <a href="http://www.compulinks.com">CompuLink Services</a>.<br><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left>Contact <a href="mailto:webmaster@compulinks.com">webmaster@compulinks.com</a> with comments.<br><img src="../images/spacer.gif" width=95 height=2 align=left><a href="http://www.compulinks.com"><img src="../images