<html><head><title>The Informed Investor Newsletter - Asset Allocation Planner</title></head><body background="../images/tile.gif" bgcolor=#ffffff link=#297b63 vlink=#297b63 alink=#31ad84><a href="../index.html"><img src="../images/home.gif" align=right border=0 alt="Home" vspace=5 hspace=5></a>&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <img src="../titles/asset.gif"><p><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=6><tr><td><img src="../images/spacer.gif"></td><td><font face=Arial><b>Conservative portfolio</b></font><hr noshade color=#297b63><font face="Arial" size=-1>Designed for regular income, where an investor will accept a lower return in return for capital safety and stability of returns. Any equity investment should be limited to high quality dividend-paying investments.<p></font><center><table border=3 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=1 background="../images/tbltile.gif" bgcolor=#c6d6c6 width=340><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Asset<br>Class</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Minimum/<br>Maximum</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Recommended<br>Weighting</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Cash equivalents</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>5 to 30%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>20%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Fixed Income</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>50 to 75%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>60%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Canadian Equities</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>10 to 30%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>20%</td></tr></table></center><p><br><font face=Arial><b>Ballanced portfolio</b></font><hr noshade color=#297b63><font face="Arial" size=-1>For investors with a fairly low risk tolerance who want a good balance between stocks and bonds. the objective is capital growth with the lowest possible investment volatility.<p></font><center><table border=3 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=1 background="../images/tbltile.gif" bgcolor=#c6d6c6 width=340><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Asset<br>Class</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Minimum/<br>Maximum</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Recommended<br>Weighting</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Cash equivalents</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>5 to 30%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>15%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Fixed Income</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>25 to 60%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>40%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Canadian Equities</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>10 to 30%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>40%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>American Equities</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>5 to 20%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>5%</td></tr></table></center><p><br><font face=Arial><b>Growth portfolio</b></font><hr noshade color=#297b63><font face="Arial" size=-1>For investors whose main interest is capital growth, while earning a small amount of income. Growth investors will accept somewhat more risk, in exchange for a better capital return.<p></font><center><table border=3 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=1 background="../images/tbltile.gif" bgcolor=#c6d6c6 width=340><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Asset<br>Class</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Minimum/<br>Maximum</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Recommended<br>Weighting</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Cash equivalents</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>0 to 30%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>10%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Fixed Income</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>20 to 50%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>35%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Canadian Equities</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>20 to 60%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>30%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>American Equities</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>5 to 30%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>10%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>International Equities</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>5 to 30%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>15%</td></tr></table></center><p><br><font face=Arial><b>Aggressive Growth portfolio</b></font><hr noshade color=#297b63><font face="Arial" size=-1>For investors seeking capital growth above all else. Much higher volatility is accepted in return for well above average capital gains. To maximize returns, an aggressive investor may also commit to holding all assets in one single asset class.<p></font><center><table border=3 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=1 background="../images/tbltile.gif" bgcolor=#c6d6c6 width=340><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Asset<br>Class</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Minimum/<br>Maximum</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Recommended<br>Weighting</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Cash equivalents</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>0 to 100%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>5%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Fixed Income</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>0 to 100%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>25%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>Canadian Equities</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>0 to 100%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>30%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>American Equities</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>0 to 100%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>15%</td></tr><tr align=center><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>International Equities</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>0 to 100%</td><td><font face="Arial" size=-1><b>25%</td></tr></table></center><p><br><font face=Arial><b>Adjustment for age</b></font><hr noshade color=#297b63><font face="Arial" size=-1>A popular asset allocation yardstick adjusts the equity portion of the portfolio for age. The rationale is that as you age, equity (and risk) should be reduced. However, even elderly investors need some equity investments to hedge against inflation.<p>The formula is: 100 years minus current age = equity allocation. For example 100 years minus 45 years = 55 years. A 45 year old should have a portfolio of 55% equities; 35% bonds; 10% money market. The mix for a 70 year old is 30% stocks: 60% bonds: 10% cash.<p><br></font><font face=Arial><b>Which funds to buy?</b></font><hr noshade color=#297b63><font face="Arial" size=-1><b><a href="bestfund.html">The Informed Investor's Best Funds List</a></b> includes both load and no load funds that have met strict criteria designed to select mutual funds that have the best combination of long term consistency and high performance. Because investors can deal with a wide choice of fund companies I have not recommended a "best fund" in any particular sector. <b>The Best Funds List represents the top 10% of long term mutual fund performers</b>. New fund purchases can be selected from this list. Compare your current mutual fund holdings with the Best Funds list, but do not switch for only minor improvements in fund performance.</font><td> &nbsp</td><td background="../images/tbltile.gif" bgcolor=#c6d6c6 valign=top><center><img src="../images/spacer.gif"><br><img src="../images/charts.gif"><font face="Arial" size=-1><hr noshade color=#297b63></center>There are no<br>charts related<br>to this article.</font><p></td></tr></table><p><p><img src="../images/spacer.gif" align=left><hr noshade color=#297b63><table border=0 width=100%><tr><td align=center><img src="../images/spacer.gif" align=left><a href="inter.html"><img src="../images/back.gif" border=0 align=left></a><a href="bestfund.html"><img src="../images/next.gif" border=0 align=right></a><a href="index.html#contents"><img src="../images/contents.gif" border=0></a></td></tr></table><p><p><img src="../images/spacer.gif" align=left><center><address><font size=-1><a href="../copyright.html">Copyright and Disclaimer</a></center><img src="../images/spacer.gif" align=left><hr noshade color=#297b63><center><img src="../images/spacer.gif" align=left>Site design by <a href="http://www.compulinks.com">CompuLink Services</a>.<br><img src="../images/spacer.gif" align=left>Contact <a href="mailto:webmaster@compulinks.com">webmaster@compulinks.com</a> with comments.<br><img src="../images/spacer.gif" align=left><a href="http://www.compulinks.com"><img src="../images/smllogo.gif" border=0 vspace=5 alt="CompuLink Services"></a></address></font><p><font color=#ffffff>47</center></body></html>>
