<HEAD><TITLE>Conference  of Radiation Control</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY><PRE><H2>
    Conference of Radiation Control Program Directors, Inc. (CRCPD)</H2><H3>
                           Contract DE-FC01-93RW00284 (Since 1989)</H3>
<P>
The Conference of Radiation Control Program Directors (CRCPD) is a non-profit organization
made up of state and local government representatives who regulate and control the use of
radiation sources.  The Conference is comprised of radiation control program directors in all states,
New York City, the California counties of Los Angeles, Orange and San Diego, the District of
Columbia, and the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico. The Conference is active in the  review of
emergency response procedures for shipment of radioactive material, and in the establishment of
standards for radiological inspections.
<P>
<B>Contact: Terry Devine, CRCPD Project Manager - 502/227-4543, Fax 502/227-7862
         Aubrey Godwin (AZ) , Committee Chairperson - 602/255-4845, Fax 602/437-0705</B> 
<HR>
<U>FY 96 3rd Quarter Activities (April-June 1996):</U>
<P>
4/96   Attended the COHMED Conference  (Mark Yeager, Raleigh, NC).
<P>
4/96   Commenced preparation and development of tasks and budget for new fiscal year.
<HR>
<B>FY 96 4th Quarter Scheduled Activities (July-September 1996):</B>
<P>
7/96   Attend the Transportation External Coordination Working Group meeting in Pittsburgh,
       PA.
<P>
8/96   Update list of short courses on radiation materials.
<P>
8/96   Draft brochure on radiation risk in transportation.
<HR>
<B>Activities for current budget period:</B>
<P>
1.  Provide review and comment on OCRWM documents as requested.
<P>
2.  Conduct biannual committee meetings and provide minutes of the proceedings.
<P>
3.  Participate in Transportation External Coordination Working Group and other meetings as
    necessary.
<P>
4.  Prepare:
<P>
  - videotape:  First Response to Transportation Accidents Involving Radioactive Materials
    (completed 12/95) 
<P>
  - generic radiation risk document (published: Health Risks of Low-Level Ionizing Radiation) 
<P>
  - brochure on high-level radioactive waste transportation (under development)
<P>
5.  Publish and distribute Directory of State Agencies Involved in Transportation of Radioactive
    Material, With Notes on their Statutory Authority (completed 10/95).
</PRE></BODY>
</HTML>
